            Individuals - students, interns, trainees, adults, young people, volunteers, teachers, trainers, youth workers, professionals from organizations active in the field of education, training and youth make the main target group of the program. It should be kept in mind, however, individuals can not apply directly for the grant of financial support, but they must contact their institution (eg university), organization or company which can submit the application.
            Institutions eligible for participation in Erasmus + projects must primarily belong to the program countries (Members of the European Union, FYR Macedonia, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway and Turkey), while some parts of the program, especially those related to higher education, are open to participants from the partner countries (partner countries can be those located in the neighborhood of the European Union, but also all other countries of the world. This category includes Bosnia and Herzegovina).
